===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|brægen|bræġen|brain|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|bragnan|brain|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|mreghmno-|skull, brain|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|mreK-|marrow, sinciput|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|braine|lang=sco}}, {{term|brane||brain|lang=sco}}, West Frisian {{term|brein||brain|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|brein||brain|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|brägen||brain|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|βρεχμος||tr=brechmos|front part of the skull, top of the head|lang=grc}}.

